{"_id":"NzgxZjA5N2Y0MDVk","name":"Rollable Encounter Tables","permission":{"default":0},"folder":"YjUwZWEyYWY3ZGVm","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":6,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":60000,"entryTime":0,"content":"\n<section class=\"secret\"><p>GM Notes : </p><h2 style=\"font-family: &#34;helvetica neue&#34; , &#34;helvetica&#34; , &#34;arial&#34; , sans-serif\">Rollable Random Encounter Tables &amp; Macros</h2><p>With <i>Waterdeep: Dragon Heist</i>, Roll20 has provided all Random Encounters as rollable tables for ease of use, found in the \"Collections\" tab. In this handout are also Macros for GMs to add to their game as they see fit. Be sure to check the specific handout for random encounters each set of random encounters for any additional information.</p><hr><h3 style=\"font-family: &#34;helvetica neue&#34; , &#34;helvetica&#34; , &#34;arial&#34; , sans-serif\">How To Use</h3><p>There are two ways that rollable tables and these macros can be used:<br>Rolling from the rollable tables will provide you with the text on the encounter. However, rolling this way always displays this roll to players.<br>Rolling using a macro allows you to roll so only the GM can see the results of the roll. These macros also will roll to see if an encounter occurs as a whisper to the GM.&nbsp;</p><p>The included code for macros will only display to the GM. Learn more about macros on the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://wiki.roll20.net/Macros\">Roll20 wiki article</a>. If you'd like to customize the macros for your use, see the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://wiki.roll20.net/D%26D_5e_OGL_Roll_Templates\">Roll20 Wiki D&amp;D 5e OGL Roll Templates</a>&nbsp;for more information.</p><p>For faster access to macros, make sure there is a checkmark next to \"Show macro quick bar?\" and check \"In Bar\" next to each macro to display them in a box at the bottom of your screen.</p><hr><p style=\"font-family: &#34;helvetica neue&#34; , &#34;helvetica&#34; , &#34;arial&#34; , sans-serif\"><i style=\"font-size: 13px ; color: rgb( 0 , 0 , 0 )\">The following macros are in the main module and are used across all seasons.</i></p><h3 style=\"font-family: &#34;helvetica neue&#34; , &#34;helvetica&#34; , &#34;arial&#34; , sans-serif\">Faction Missions</h3><h4 style=\"font-family: &#34;helvetica neue&#34; , &#34;helvetica&#34; , &#34;arial&#34; , sans-serif\">Emerald Enclave: Scarecrow Encounter Chance</h4><pre>/w gm &amp;{template:npcaction} {{rname= Emerald Enclave-2nd Level Mission }} {{name= Scarecrow Encounter Chance }} {{description= If the characters camp in a field for the better part of a day or night, they encounter one of the three scarecrows at a 10% chance (roll of 90 or better). [[1d100]]. For more information, see the ***[Emerald&amp;#8288; Enclave](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-LJ6vk0rYIye8Yi_ni9T)*** handout. }}</pre><h4>Emerald Enclave: Skeleton Encounter Chance</h4><pre>/w gm &amp;{template:npcaction} {{rname= Emerald Enclave-3rd Level Mission }} {{name= Skeleton Encounter Chance }} {{description= The characters have a cumulative 10% chance of encountering the skeletons each night they patrol and do so on a roll of 90 or better. [[ 1d100+[[?{Number of nights on patrol?|0}*10]] ]]. For more information, see the ***[Emerald&amp;#8288; Enclave](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-LJ6vk0rYIye8Yi_ni9T)*** handout. }}</pre><h4>Harpers: Chance of Mirt Being Home</h4><pre>/w gm &amp;{template:npcaction} {{rname= Harpers }} {{name= Is Mirt Home? }} {{description= There is only a 10% chance (roll of 90 or better) Mirt is home and someone will answer the door to his Sea Ward manor. [[1d100 ]] For more information, see the ***[Harpers&amp;#8288;](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-LJ6vyZzqdkumgb7HdSl)*** and ***[Mirt&amp;#8288;](http://journal.roll20.net/character/-LIb4TYMF9AI4vKnUeaH)***&nbsp; handouts. }}</pre><p><br></p><h3>Running A Business</h3><h4>Business Success</h4><pre>/w gm &amp;{template:npcaction} {{rname= Running A Business }} {{name= Profits/Losses }} {{description= [[ 1d100+10+?{GP spent on promotion?|0}-?{GP owed in debts?|0}+?{Any other modifiers?|0} ]]. For results, see the ***[Running&amp;#8288; A Business](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-LJVCOKogKih_dEOqe-k)*** handout. For profits, use the Profit Margins macro. }}</pre><h4>Profit Margins</h4><pre>/w gm &amp;{template:npcaction} {{rname= Running A Business }} {{name= Profit Margins }} {{description= The tavern makes [[ ?{Results from Profits/Losses roll?|61-80,[[1d6]]*5|81-90,[[2d8]]*5|91+,[[3d10]]*5}*?{Number of days run?|0} ]] gp this tenday. }}</pre><p><br></p><h3>Gralhund Villa</h3><h4>Rounds Until the City Watch Arrives</h4><pre>/w gm &amp;{template:npcaction} {{rname= City Watch Arrives }} {{name= Gralhund Villa }} {{description= The City Watch will arrive in [[ [[1d6+4]]*10 ]] combat rounds with a sergeant and five constables (**mage** and six **veterans**). For more information, see the ***[Gralhund&amp;#8288; Villa](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-LJ6xiQi7h382RPtNOxg)*** handout and ***[Time](https://roll20.net/compendium/dnd5e/Rules:Time?expansion=0#content)*** in the compendium. }}</pre><p><span style=\"font-family: &#34;helvetica neue&#34; , &#34;helvetica&#34; , &#34;arial&#34; , sans-serif\"><br></span></p><h3><span style=\"font-family: &#34;helvetica neue&#34; , &#34;helvetica&#34; , &#34;arial&#34; , sans-serif\">The Vault of Dragons</span></h3><h4><span style=\"font-family: &#34;helvetica neue&#34; , &#34;helvetica&#34; , &#34;arial&#34; , sans-serif\">Villain's Timetable</span></h4><pre>/w gm &amp;{template:npcaction} {{rname= Villain's Timetable }} {{name= On Acquiring Stone }} {{description= If the villain(s) acquire the *Stone of Golorr*, they take [[ 2d6 ]] to find the Vault of Dragons and its keys and [[ 2d6 ]] days to defeat Aurinax and recover the gold before moving forward on their master plans. For more information, see the ***[Encounter&amp;#8288; Chains](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-LJrOMvl2Cpbqp2iVc7K)*** handout as well as details on plans in their add-ons. }}</pre><h4><span style=\"font-family: &#34;helvetica neue&#34; , &#34;helvetica&#34; , &#34;arial&#34; , sans-serif\">Combined Vault Keys</span></h4><pre>/w gm &amp;{template:npcaction} {{rname= Vault of Dragons }} {{name= Keys }} {{description= The first key is [[1t[VoD-First-Key]]]. The second key is [[1t[VoD-Second-Key]]]. The third key is [[1t[VoD-Third-Key]]]. For more information, see the ***[Vault&amp;#8288; Keys](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-LJ71qc9QZp9O5_oz5VP)*** handout. }}</pre><h4><span style=\"font-family: &#34;helvetica neue&#34; , &#34;helvetica&#34; , &#34;arial&#34; , sans-serif\">First Key</span></h4><pre>/w gm &amp;{template:npcaction} {{rname= Vault of Dragons }} {{name= First Key }} {{description= The first key is [[1t[VoD-First-Key]]]. For more information, see the ***[Vault&amp;#8288; Keys](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-LJ71qc9QZp9O5_oz5VP)*** handout. }}</pre><h4><span style=\"font-family: &#34;helvetica neue&#34; , &#34;helvetica&#34; , &#34;arial&#34; , sans-serif\">Second Key</span></h4><pre>/w gm &amp;{template:npcaction} {{rname= Vault of Dragons }} {{name= Keys }} {{description= The second key is [[1t[VoD-Second-Key]]]. For more information, see the ***[Vault&amp;#8288; Keys](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-LJ71qc9QZp9O5_oz5VP)*** handout. }}</pre><h4><span style=\"font-family: &#34;helvetica neue&#34; , &#34;helvetica&#34; , &#34;arial&#34; , sans-serif\">Third Key</span></h4><pre>/w gm &amp;{template:npcaction} {{rname= Vault of Dragons }} {{name= Keys }} {{description= The third key is [[1t[VoD-Third-Key]]]. For more information, see the ***[Vault&amp;#8288; Keys](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-LJ71qc9QZp9O5_oz5VP)*** handout. }}</pre><h4><span style=\"font-family: &#34;helvetica neue&#34; , &#34;helvetica&#34; , &#34;arial&#34; , sans-serif\">Villain's Pursuers</span></h4><pre>/w gm &amp;{template:npcaction} {{rname= Vault of Dragons }} {{name= Villain's Pursuit }} {{description= ?{Which season?|Spring,Xanathar sends [[ 1t[VoD-Spring-Pursuit] ]]|Summer,The Cassalanters send [[ 1t[VoD-Summer-Pursuit] ]]|Autumn,Jarlaxle Baenre sends **Fel’rekt Lafeen and Krebbyg Masq’il’yr (or two other Bregan D’aerthe drow gunslingers) and six drow**|Winter,Manshoon sends [[ 1t[VoD-Winter-Pursuit] ]]}. For more information, see the ***[Vault&amp;#8288; Keys](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-LJ71qc9QZp9O5_oz5VP)*** handout. }}</pre><hr><p><i>The macros for each season are customized specifically for that season.</i></p><h3>Spring Madness</h3><h4>Encounter 2: Mistshore-Grinda's Apparatus</h4><pre>/w gm &amp;{template:npcaction} {{rname= Mistshore }} {{name= Borrowing Grinda's Apparatus }} {{description= The characters search the harbor for a day. The pilot leads them to find [[ [[1d20+@{selected|investigation_prof}]]*10 ]] gp worth of treasure, which Grinda sells and takes half of. During the day, [[1t[MS-Shark-Attack]]]. For more information, see the ***[Areas&amp;#8288; of Mistshore](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-LJBWw4EkoZrSv3tfCBZ)*** handout. }}</pre><h4>Encounter 4: Masoleum-Encountering Sir Everdawn</h4><pre>/w gm &amp;{template:npcaction} {{rname= Mausoleum }} {{name= Encountering Sir Ambrose Everdawn }} {{description= [[1d100]]. On a roll of 70 or more between sunrise and sunset, the characters encounter the knight **[Sir Ambrose Everdawn](http://journal.roll20.net/character/-LIO1nRsDnPrwOtX7UUy)** while in the cemetary. He escorts them out and alerts the City Guard if they refuse to leave. For more information, see ***[Areas&amp;#8288; of the Mausoleum](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-LJBWCUJjbMbVL76LJd6)*** handout. }}</pre><h4>Encounter 3: Street Chase-Complications</h4><pre>/w gm &amp;{template:npcaction} {{rname= Street Chase }} {{name= Chase Complications }} {{description= [[1t[SC-Chase-Complications-Table]]] For more information, see the ***[Street&amp;#8288; Chase](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-LJQits8kCNt43eHuUQW)*** and ***[Urban&amp;#8288; Chase Complications and Rules](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-LJVIy6ohVpBjlnzqW03)*** handouts. }}</pre><h4>Encounter 7: Old Tower-Treasure</h4><pre>/w gm &amp;{template:npcaction} {{rname= The Old Tower }} {{name= Treasure Table }} {{description= [[1t[OT-Treasure-Table]]] For more information, see the ***[Areas&amp;#8288; of the Old Tower](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-LJBX42UvASsJpJT7UnJ)*** handout. }}</pre><h4>Encounter 7: Old Tower-Potion Miscibility</h4><pre>/w gm &amp;{template:npcaction} {{rname= The Old Tower }} {{name= Potion Miscibility }} {{description= If the mixed *potion of healing* and *potion of flying* from the Old Tower is imbibed, [[1t[Potion-Miscibility-Table]]] For more information, see the ***[Potion&amp;#8288; Miscibility](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-LJVGQNxic5uX3g9nSwW)*** handout. }}</pre><h4>Encounter 1: Alley-Store Goods</h4><pre>/w gm &amp;{template:npcaction} {{rname= Alley }} {{name= Store Goods }} {{description= The store in the Alley (area **L2**) sells [[1t[Alley-Store-Goods]]] For more information, see the ***[Areas&amp;#8288; of the Alley](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-LIi6HmI7Jb4KaH4XXkx)*** handout. }}</pre><h4>Xanathar's Lair-Xanathar's Location</h4><pre>/w gm &amp;{template:npcaction} {{rname= Facing Xanathar }} {{name= Xanathar's Location }} {{description= Within its lair, [[1t[SM-Xanathar-Location-Table]]] For more information, see the ***[Facing&amp;#8288; Xanathar](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-LJBXnGAJzFj7WAJV1IZ)*** handout. }}</pre><h4>Special Event: Trolltide Backup</h4><pre>/w gm &amp;{template:npcaction} {{rname= Random Loot }} {{name= Name of Loot Table }} {{description= [[1d100]] On a roll of 80 or more on the initiative count of the City Watch **veterans**, another will arrive and join the fray. For more information, see the ***[Special&amp;#8288; Events](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-LJQqLGI60xV44BwL2Q8)*** handout. }}</pre><hr><h3>Hell of a Summer</h3><h4>E