l20.net/handout/-LJBZrkWRoaBwptXfyZ2)*** handout. }}</pre><h4>Encounter 10: Converted Windmill-Attempted Break-In</h4><pre>/w gm &amp;{template:npcaction} {{rname= Converted Windmill }} {{name= Break-In Attempt }} {{description= When attempting to break in, [[1t[CW-Break-In-Attempt]]] For more information, see the ***[Converted&amp;#8288; Windmill](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-LKAob1V7NFyBx1Zo9Kl)*** handout. }}</pre><h4>Encounter 10: Converted Windmill-Painting Subjects</h4><pre>/w gm &amp;{template:npcaction} {{rname= Random Loot }} {{name= Name of Loot Table }} {{description= The subject of the painting in this room is a [[1t[CW-Painting-Subjects-Table]]]. For more information, see the ***[Converted&amp;#8288; Windmill](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-LKAob1V7NFyBx1Zo9Kl)*** handout. }}</pre><h4>Sea Maiden's Faire: Chance of a Jailed Sailor</h4><pre>/w gm &amp;{template:npcaction} {{rname= Random Loot }} {{name= Name of Loot Table }} {{description= [[1d100]] On a roll of 76 or higher, a jailed **drow** sailor in the brig of the ship. For more information, see the ***[Areas&amp;#8288; of the Ships](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-LJBaTwZZonob11SgZSh)*** handout. }}</pre><hr><h3>Winter Wizardry</h3><h4>Encounter 1: Alley-Store Goods</h4><pre>/w gm &amp;{template:npcaction} {{rname= Alley }} {{name= Store Goods }} {{description= The store in the Alley (area **L2**) sells [[1t[Alley-Store-Goods]]] For more information, see the ***[Areas&amp;#8288; of the Alley](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-LIiKEDyzVV9cJItqK04)*** handout. }}</pre><h4>Encounter 5: Rooftop Chase-Complications</h4><pre>/w gm &amp;{template:npcaction} {{rname= Rooftop Chase }} {{name= Chase Complications }} {{description= [[1t[RC-Chase-Complications-Table]]] For more information, see the ***[Rooftop&amp;#8288; Chase](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-LJA7R5NU0Sff4cknpEb)*** handout. }}</pre><h4>Encounter 3: Street Chase-Complications</h4><pre>/w gm &amp;{template:npcaction} {{rname= Street Chase }} {{name= Chase Complications }} {{description= [[1t[SC-Chase-Complications-Table]]] For more information, see the ***[Street&amp;#8288; Chase](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-LJPwX-2mLoXgWrQdjxy)*** and ***[Urban&amp;#8288; Chase Complications and Rules](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-LJVIy6ohVpBjlnzqW03)*** handouts. }}</pre><h4>Encounter 2: Mistshore-Grinda's Apparatus</h4><pre>/w gm &amp;{template:npcaction} {{rname= Mistshore }} {{name= Borrowing Grinda's Apparatus }} {{description= The characters search the harbor for a day. The pilot leads them to find [[ [[1d20+@{selected|investigation_prof}]]*10 ]] gp worth of treasure, which Grinda sells and takes half of. During the day, [[1t[MS-Shark-Attack]]]. For more information, see the ***[Areas&amp;#8288; of Mistshore](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-LJBcGjL6l6oVDOjo-tQ)*** handout. }}</pre><h4>Encounter 7: Old Tower-Treasure</h4><pre>/w gm &amp;{template:npcaction} {{rname= The Old Tower }} {{name= Treasure Table }} {{description= [[1t[OT-Treasure-Table]]] For more information, see the ***[Areas&amp;#8288; of the Old Tower](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-LJBbrygqMNoUdXPDB91)*** handout. }}</pre><h4>Encounter 7: Old Tower-Potion Miscibility</h4><pre>/w gm &amp;{template:npcaction} {{rname= The Old Tower }} {{name= Potion Miscibility }} {{description= If the mixed *potion of healing* and *potion of flying* from the Old Tower is imbibed, [[1t[Potion-Miscibility-Table]]] For more information, see the ***[Potion&amp;#8288; Miscibility](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-LJBbrygqMNoUdXPDB91)*** handout. }}</pre><h4>Encounter 4: Masoleum-Encountering Sir Everdawn</h4><pre>/w gm &amp;{template:npcaction} {{rname= Mausoleum }} {{name= Encountering Sir Ambrose Everdawn }} {{description= [[1d100]]. On a roll of 70 or more between sunrise and sunset, the characters encounter the knight **[Sir Ambrose Everdawn](http://journal.roll20.net/character/-LIO1nRsDnPrwOtX7UUy)** while in the cemetary. He escorts them out and alerts the City Guard if they refuse to leave. For more information, see ***[Areas&amp;#8288; of the Mausoleum](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-LJBc3pVe8_k6I9LrM4Q)*** handout. }}</pre><h4>Winter Wizardry-Digging Under The Tower Barrier</h4><pre>/w gm &amp;{template:npcaction} {{rname= Winter Wizardry }} {{name= Digging Under Kolat Towers }} {{description= When attempting to dig under the force field, [[1t[WW-Digging-Under-Chance]]] For more information, see the ***[Kolat&amp;#8288; Towers](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-LIm_KmcpJlD9GZHX8ex)*** handout. }}</pre><h4>Winter Wizardry-Lady Gondafrey's Alignment</h4><pre>/w gm &amp;{template:npcaction} {{rname= Winter Wizardry }} {{name= Lady Gondafrey's Allignment }} {{description= [[1t[WW-Lady-Gondafrey-Alignment]]] This is rerolled each day. For more information, see the ***[Kolat&amp;#8288; Towers](http://journal.roll20.net/handout/-LIm_KmcpJlD9GZHX8ex)*** handout. }}</pre></section>","img":""}
