{"_id":"OTAyZTdmZTM1OWJm","name":"Street Chase","permission":{"default":0},"folder":"YWRjNmU3NzY1M2Y3","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":0,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":0,"entryTime":0,"content":"\n<section class=\"secret\"><p>GM Notes : </p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38 ; margin-top: 0pt ; margin-bottom: 0pt\"></p><p><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\">For this encounter, use the chase rules and the Urban Chase Complications table from the <i>Dungeon Master’s Guide</i>. The chase plays out as a “theater of the mind” experience. Consequently, you don’t need a map to run the encounter. The chase occurs outdoors, so be mindful of any weather effects in play.<br></span></p><h3><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\">Street Chase: Spring</span></h3><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\">A <b><a class=\"entity-link\" data-entity=Actor data-id=YTg2ZDU4OTJkMDM5 ><i class=\"fas fa-user\"></i>kenku</a></b> in cahoots with the Xanathar Guild has the <i>Stone of Golorr</i> and is running through the streets with it. The kenku is 60 feet away from the characters at the start of the chase.<br></span><br>If at any point the kenku is incapacitated, another kenku previously hidden by the rain or fog joins the chase, acting next in the initiative count. It suddenly appears, snatches the stone, and flees with it.<br><br><h4>Next Encounter</h4>When the characters are close to catching the kenku, or when you want the chase to end, the creature ducks into an old tower. Proceed with encounter 7, \"<a class=\"entity-link\" data-entity=JournalEntry data-id=MTFkNTVhZGZkMDFi ><i class=\"fas fa-book-open\"></i>Old Tower</a>\".<p></p></section>","img":""}
