{"_id":"ZDcwNDVmYTQ3MDBm","name":"Assassin's Blood","permission":{"default":0},"folder":"M2RjZTkxOTFlYmEx","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":2,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":20000,"entryTime":0,"content":"\n<section class=\"secret\"><p>GM Notes : </p><h3 style=\"font-family: &#34;helvetica neue&#34; , &#34;helvetica&#34; , &#34;arial&#34; , sans-serif\">Assassin's Blood</h3><p style=\"color: rgb( 64 , 64 , 64 )\">Assassin's Blood is an ingested poison. A creature must swallow an entire dose of ingested poison to suffer its effects. You might decide that a partial dose has a reduced effect, such as allowing advantage on the saving throw or dealing only half damage on a failed save.</p><p style=\"color: rgb( 64 , 64 , 64 )\">One dose of Assassin's Blood costs 150 gp.</p><p style=\"color: rgb( 64 , 64 , 64 )\">A creature subjected to this poison must make a DC 10 Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, it takes 6 (1d12) poison damage and is poisoned for 24 hours. On a successful save, the creature takes half damage and isn't poisoned.</p></section>","img":""}
